From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 13:20:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 29/29] Fix Pulse ~90s shutdown hang on SIGTERM (graceful)

Upstream issue: (pai-nix — local reliability fix; no upstream issue.)

Diagnosis (2026-06-12): on system shutdown systemd sends SIGTERM to
pai-pulse.service, then waits the full TimeoutStopSec (default 90s)
before SIGKILL. Confirmed across boots -1/-2/-3 in journalctl
("pai-pulse.service: State 'stop-sigterm' timed out. Killing."). This
~90s was the dominant contributor to slow shutdowns.

Root cause: PULSE/pulse.ts registers a SIGTERM handler, but the handler
only sets `shuttingDown = true`. The main loop is usually parked in
`await Bun.sleep(sleepMs)` (sleepMs scales up to MAX_SLEEP_MS while the
scheduler waits for the next due job), and setting the flag does not
interrupt that sleep. So the loop never re-evaluates `while
(!shuttingDown)` in time, never reaches its cleanup, and never exits
before the 90s SIGKILL.

Fix (graceful, code-only — deliberately NOT a systemd TimeoutStopSec
safety-net):
  - shutdown() now calls wakeFromSleep() to interrupt the parked sleep.
  - the main-loop sleep becomes an interruptible Promise (clearTimeout +
    resolve on signal), so on SIGTERM/SIGINT the loop wakes immediately,
    runs the existing cleanup (server.stop, module stops, writeState),
    and returns.
  - a final process.exit(0) after cleanup guarantees the runtime exits
    promptly even if a module leaves a live handle.

Result: shutdown completes in well under a second instead of ~90s.
---
diff --git a/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PULSE/pulse.ts b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PULSE/pulse.ts
--- a/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PULSE/pulse.ts
+++ b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PULSE/pulse.ts
@@ -321,11 +321,13 @@
 
   // Graceful shutdown
   let shuttingDown = false
+  let wakeFromSleep: () => void = () => {}
   const isShuttingDown = () => shuttingDown
   const shutdown = () => {
     if (shuttingDown) return
     shuttingDown = true
     log("info", "Shutting down gracefully")
+    wakeFromSleep() // prekini dolg Bun.sleep v glavni zanki → cleanup steče takoj (sicer systemd čaka 90s TimeoutStopSec → SIGKILL)
   }
   process.on("SIGTERM", shutdown)
   process.on("SIGINT", shutdown)
@@ -531,7 +533,14 @@
     const sleepMs = Math.max(MIN_SLEEP_MS, Math.min(nextDueMs - elapsed, MAX_SLEEP_MS))
 
     if (!shuttingDown) {
-      await Bun.sleep(sleepMs)
+      // prekinljiv sleep: SIGTERM/SIGINT zbudi takoj (sicer zanka visi do MAX_SLEEP_MS)
+      await new Promise<void>((resolve) => {
+        const timer = setTimeout(resolve, sleepMs)
+        wakeFromSleep = () => {
+          clearTimeout(timer)
+          resolve()
+        }
+      })
     }
   }
 
@@ -543,6 +552,7 @@
   if (syslogModule) await syslogModule.stop?.()
   await writeState(STATE_PATH, state).catch(() => {})
   log("info", "PAI Pulse stopped", { uptimeMs: Date.now() - state.startedAt })
+  process.exit(0) // po graceful cleanupu zagotovi izhod, tudi če kak modul pusti živ handle
 }
 
 main().catch((err) => {
